snippet.textDisplay:
On the topic of male beauty standards, I didn't find that model attractive. I understand why someone else would find him attractive, but to me I think he's a little too naturally photoshopped, if that makes sense. I mean, the photo was probably edited somewhat, anyway, but the fact everything on Mike's face looked so perfect unsettles me a little. I find if someone is too symmetrical, I get a little unnerved by them and I find i'd be less likely to trust said person if I met them irl.

Using Mark and Ethan as examples (for easy references); If asked who was more attractive, I think alot of people would would say Mark, and I understand that choice because Mark has a stronger jawline, a nicely sculpted face, the beard suits him well, and alot of people like a more toned body.
However, I think if I was asked, i'd pick Ethan, just because he's more 'my type'. I use the term 'type' loosely, because I think it's expanding as i'm maturing, but my type is usually more along the lines of what Ethan looks like. He's got a slender figure, but you can still see a soft outline of his muscles (whereas I don't like muscley guys); you can see his jawline, but it's not too prominent; he's got nice eyebrows (they're not too bushy, and they're a nice shape without being too shapely), his eyes are really pretty, and I like nice smooth cheeks that have a little bit of squish to pinch (yes, that's a technical term. I'm writing this before sleep).

I find it really interesting to have discussions about this kind of thing because I think it's really interesting to see what other people find attractive, so please, if you have an input, feel free to join in (but no negative comments please).
